                   "message":  "docs: external-engine lessons ledger (harvest practice, five-pressure frame)\n\nAdd docs/EXTERNAL_ENGINE_LESSONS.md -- a capture backlog for patterns observed in\ncomparable engines (OpenClaw first), each mapped to the RGE locus it could\npressure-test. Mirrors kariyer\u0027s \"automation for ideas\" (capture -\u003e stage -\u003e\npromote), adapted to RGE\u0027s architecture freeze: design docs + code change ONLY on\n`promoted`, and promotion requires demonstrated pressure (PLAN section 0.6), not\nforecast. Reporter / backlog, not a gate -- it authorizes nothing.\n\nOrganizes lessons by five recurring kernel pressures (composition, declarative\ncontent, subsystem boundaries, execution-time, authority-arbitration) and uses a\ntwo-gate promotion model: Gate A (phase/roadmap) drives cheap preparation\n(mine + design-stage, commits nothing); Gate B (section 0.6 pressure) drives the\ncommit (ADR/PLAN/build). Guardrails keep staging from sliding into forecast\nexpansion.\n\nSeeded with 6 rows from the OpenClaw\u003c-\u003eRGE comparison, incl. LES-005 (a recorded\ndeliberate divergence -- RGE does physics-as-plugin, not a facade) and LES-006\n(authority-arbitration: the no-donor row where RGE cannot borrow blindly).\n\nDocs-only; no code, no new lint, no parallel authority.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
